{"outcome":{"note":{}},"id":"52-849","phase":"decompose","detail":"thinking: ## DECOMPOSER Report — Issue #52: `chunkText` drops consecutive punctuation\n\n### 1. Project context\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Language** | TypeScript (strict) |\n| **Framework** | SvelteKit (`apps\/web`), Node ≥20 monorepo (npm workspaces) |\n| **Test runner** | Vitest (`apps\/web\/vitest.config.ts`), with jsdom |\n| **Build command** | `npm run build:web` → `node scripts\/publish-catalog.mjs && npm run -w apps\/web build` |\n| **Test command** | `npm run test` → `vitest run` in `apps\/web` |\n| **Affected files** | **1 source file**, **1 test file** (see below) |\n| **Blast radius** | 1 caller: `prepareForSynthesis()` in `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts` |\n\n### 2. Affected files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts` | The buggy implementation (~120 lines) |\n| `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.test.ts` | Existing test suite (~160 lines, 16 tests) |\n\n### 3. Root cause (confirmed)\n\nThe sentence-segmentation regex on **line 69**:\n\n```ts\nconst segments = trimmed.match(\/\\s*[^.!?\\s][^.!?]*[.!?]?\/g) ?? [];\n```\n\nhas two defects that compound:\n\n1. **`[^.!?\\s]`** — requires every segment to begin with a **non-delimiter, non-whitespace** character. When the input contains consecutive delimiters (e.g., `?!`, `..`, `. . .`), the characters after the first delimiter have no non-delimiter to anchor on, so the regex **skips them entirely**.\n\n2. **`[.!?]?`** — captures **at most one** optional trailing delimiter. Even if a segment *could* start, it would never capture `...` or `?!` as a run — only the first delimiter char.\n\n### 4. Traced behavior on the reproduction cases\n\n**`chunkText('Wait... what?', 8)`** (13 chars):\n\n| Position | Regex match | Segment |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| 0 | `\\s*[^.!?\\s][^.!?]*[.!?]?` matches `Wai`t`.` | `Wait.` |\n| 5–6 | `[^.!?\\s]` fails on `.` — **skipped** | *(lost `..`)* |\n| 7 | Matches ` ` `what` `?` | ` what?` |\n\nResult: `['Wait.', ' what?']` → join = `\"Wait. what?\"` — **lost `..`**\n\n**`chunkText('Really?! No way.', 9)`** — the `!` at position 7 is skipped because `[^.!?\\s]` fails on it.\n\n**`chunkText('End. . . done.', 6)`** — the entire `. . ` run (positions 4–7, `. . `) is skipped.\n\n### 5. Fix strategy (regex-only, no signature\/algorithm change)\n\nReplace the regex with one that (a) captures consecutive trailing delimiters greedily and (b) provides an alternative for delimiter-only runs:\n\n```ts\n\/\/ BEFORE (broken):\nconst segments = trimmed.match(\/\\s*[^.!?\\s][^.!?]*[.!?]?\/g) ?? [];\n\n\/\/ AFTER (fixed):\nconst segments = trimmed.match(\/\\s*(?:[.!?]+|[^.!?\\s][^.!?]*[.!?]*)\/g) ?? [];\n```\n\n**Why this works:**\n\n- **`[.!?]+`** (tried **first** in the alternation) captures runs of one or more consecutive delimiters. Combined with the outer `\\s*`, it absorbs optional leading whitespace before a delimiter-only segment. This catches `..`, `?!`, `. . .` etc. that the old regex silently skipped.\n\n- **`[^.!?\\s][^.!?]*[.!?]*`** (tried second) is the normal sentence segment, but with `[.!?]*` (greedy, zero-or-more) instead of `[.!?]?` (optional, at-most-one). This captures `...`, `?!`, `!!!` as part of the preceding sentence rather than dropping the extras.\n\n- The greedy `*` on trailing delimiters means `Wait...` stays as one segment instead of being split at the first dot — which is actually **more** semantically correct (ellipses belong to their sentence).\n\n### 6. Verification: invariants preserved\n\nTraced the fixed regex against all reproduction cases and edge cases:\n\n- `'Wait... what?'` → segments: `['Wait...', ' what?']` ✓ (join preserves all chars)\n- `'Really?! No way.'` → segments: `['Really?!', ' No way.']` ✓\n- `'End. . . done.'` (maxLength=6) → segments: `['End.', ' .', ' .', ' done.']` → greedy-packed chunks: `['End. .', ' .', ' done.']` ✓ (join exact, each ≤ 6)\n- `'Hello. World!'` (maxLength=7) → `['Hello.', ' World!']` ✓ (existing behavior unchanged)\n- `'...Wait'` → `['...', 'Wait']` ✓ (delimiter-only start handled)\n- `'!!!'` → `['!!!']` ✓ (pure-delimiter input handled)\n- Empty\/whitespace → `[]` ✓ (trim shortcut untouched)\n- `maxLength <= 0` → throws ✓ (guard untouched)\n- Under-limit shortcut → `[trimmed]` ✓ (untouched)\n\n### 7. Test plan (to be implemented)\n\nAdd to `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.test.ts`:\n\n1. **Three reproduction cases** from the issue, asserting `result.join('') === input`\n2. **Hard-split + punctuation run**: e.g., `chunkText('Hi...there', 4)` → chunks like `['Hi..', '.the', 're']` that preserve all chars\n3. **Property-style check**: iterate over a table of punctuation-heavy inputs (`...`, `?!`, `!!!`, `. . .`, `?!...`, etc.) at multiple `maxLength` values and assert `chunks.join('') === text`\n\n### 8. Deliverables (single deliverable — one cohesive change)\n\n| # | What | Where |\n|---|------|-------|\n| 1 | Fix the regex (line 69) | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts` |\n| 2 | Add regression + property tests | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.test.ts` |\n\nBoth changes are in the same directory, tested by the same vitest suite, and can be verified with `npm run test` + `npm run build:web`.","at":804601181.773554,"ticketId":"52"}
